Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the program, \Nbrothers and sisters!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.79,0:00:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,During the next hour, \Nyou will hear the story of a brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.89,0:00:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who previously protected \Nthe president of a country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But seeing the love among God’s people \Nmade him refocus his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to bearing witness \Nabout the Sovereign of the universe.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.90,0:00:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We cherish our international brotherhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.07,0:00:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters \Nin the former Soviet Union took great risks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.34,0:00:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,during the Cold War to convey their love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.74,0:00:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to fellow Witnesses \Non the other side of the globe.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.55,0:00:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Does our love for Jehovah motivate us \Nto avoid living a double life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.45,0:00:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This dramatization \Nwill remind us of key principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.59,0:00:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect us when we are tempted \Nto draw closer to Satan’s world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the July program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.18,0:01:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book \NInsight on the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.75,0:01:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,under the heading “Christian,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.79,0:01:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes clear that claiming to be Christian \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.06,0:01:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,requires more than simply \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a mere confession of faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.13,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is more than \Nbeing a nominal Christian\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—a Christian in name only.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.17,0:01:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Naccording to the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.63,0:01:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it is necessary that belief \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.84,0:01:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,be demonstrated by works, \Nnot just words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.41,0:01:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And since we were born \Nas sinners, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.01,0:01:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,those who become Christians \Nneed to repent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.25,0:01:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn around, \Nto dedicate their lives to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.12,0:01:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to worship and serve him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.15,0:01:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to submit \Nto water baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.49,0:01:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They must keep themselves \Nclean from fornication, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.66,0:01:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from idolatry, \Nand from consuming blood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.16,0:01:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They are to strip off \Nthe old personality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.37,0:01:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,including such things \Nas fits of anger, obscene talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.47,0:02:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,lying, stealing, drunkenness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.81,0:02:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and as Galatians chapter 5 says: \N“things like these.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.71,0:02:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they are to bring their lives \Ninto accord with Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians are to be \Nkind and considerate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,mild-tempered and patient, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and are to exercise self-control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They provide \Nand care for their own \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and love \Ntheir neighbor as themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a lot, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a matter \Nof just glibly saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.40,0:02:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am a Christian.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite all of those \Nimpressive characteristics \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that we just enumerated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.91,0:02:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what did Jesus say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the main identifying quality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.91,0:02:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of a true Christian would be? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.32,0:02:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of you know the answer to that, \Nbut let’s read it again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.49,0:02:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from John 13:34, 35. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:03:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “I am giving you \Na new commandment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you love one another; \Njust as I have loved you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.13,0:03:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“you also love one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.00,0:03:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“By this all will know \Nthat you are my disciples\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—if you have love among yourselves.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the theme verses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for my discussion \Nwith you this month. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The topic is: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Love—The Identifying Mark \Nof a Disciple of Jesus.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.92,0:03:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nin verse 34 that Jesus said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was giving them \Nat that time a “new commandment”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sounds like \Na very old commandment, doesn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.14,0:03:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, over 1,500 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,before Jesus said \Nthe words we just read, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Law given to Moses said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love \Nyour fellow man as yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.18,0:03:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—Leviticus 19:18.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what was “new” \Nabout Jesus’ command \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:03:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in John chapter 13? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.42,0:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that true Christians \Nwere to love each other \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as I have loved you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.36,0:04:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what was different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.97,0:04:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That was new, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.04,0:04:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not just love the other person \Nas you love yourself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but love him just like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.37,0:04:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus loved His followers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.21,0:04:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what kind of love \Nwould that be? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-sacrificing love\N—and usually we think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.42,0:04:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ ultimate sacrifice, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,his willingly giving his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we might have the hope \Nof everlasting life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you think about it, \Nthat aspect of Jesus’ love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was exemplified \Nin a self-sacrificing death! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it is true, \Nthat as a Christian, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.97,0:04:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we might at some time have to give \Nour life for a fellow Christian. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But we hope \Nit doesn’t come to that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:04:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of talking \Nabout a self-sacrificing death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to discuss \Nshowing this new kind of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as evidenced \Nin a self-sacrificing life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.79,0:05:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,not necessarily our death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.93,0:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Jesus’ life\N—his three-and-a-half-year ministry—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was a self-sacrificing life \Nof loving others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.34,0:05:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to doing good \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when something requires it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.48,0:05:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a true follower of Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.48,0:05:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take \Nthe initiative to help others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually and otherwise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.82,0:05:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He is to work actively \Nfor their good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The preaching and teaching \Nof the good news to others\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.22,0:05:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—some of whom may even be hostile—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the greatest expressions \Nof love, for it can result \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in everlasting life \Nto the recipients. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Naccording to Paul’s words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Thessalonians 2:8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:06:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a true Christian must \N‘impart not only the good news of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.08,0:06:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but also his very self’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in helping those who \Naccept the good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s that kind of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus said would be \Nan identifying mark of his disciples, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.09,0:06:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not specifically that his followers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would all be dying for each other, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.77,0:06:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but more so that they \Nwould all be living for each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, displaying self-sacrificing love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.31,0:06:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for one another \Nevery day of their lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.68,0:06:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The four Gospels \Nare a treasure trove \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.71,0:06:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ self-sacrificing love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, \Nthey do not cover his actions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.75,0:06:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,every day of his life \Nas the Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,His three-and-a-half-year ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,amounts to nearly \N1,300 days of life and love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The written record \Nof Jesus’ life is admittedly brief, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.03,0:07:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is grand indeed! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.70,0:07:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the reality \Nof observing Jesus every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.47,0:07:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,must have been far grander \Nthan what we have in print. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have in print \Nmight be likened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.81,0:07:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to a photo album \Nof Jesus’ life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.02,0:07:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,some snapshots. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.25,0:07:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By comparison, \Nwhat his apostles experienced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jesus day after day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a continuous video \Nof his example of love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.66,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder that, \Nat John 21:25, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the apostle said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.20,0:07:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“There are also . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“many other things that Jesus did, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“which if ever they were written \Nin full detail, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.05,0:07:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“I suppose the world itself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.45,0:07:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,could not contain the scrolls written.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.35,0:07:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It said there were \N‘many other things Jesus did,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:07:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not many other things \Nthat he said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.69,0:08:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but that he did, \Nyes, deeds or acts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.10,0:08:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrating \Nhis self-sacrificing life of love! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.77,0:08:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We already mentioned \Nthe all-important preaching work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.31,0:08:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as being an act \Nof love on our part. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.08,0:08:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But how else \Ndo we manifest \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the most obvious trait \Nof a genuine Christian\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—love like Jesus had?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.55,0:08:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start by thinking \Nof the elders in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.12,0:08:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At Philippians 2:17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.59,0:08:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul said that he \Nhad ‘poured himself out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.13,0:08:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to the congregation \Nlike a drink offering.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.40,0:08:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What did that mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.40,0:08:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It meant that he \Ndrained himself out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.21,0:08:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,both physically and emotionally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the Philippians.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the elders \Nin our congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have the same self-sacrificing love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for those under their care. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.62,0:08:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They give of their time \Nto shepherd \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.35,0:08:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and readjust those in need. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.52,0:09:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They take the lead \Nin the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They respond when there is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.86,0:09:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a serious health issue or tragedy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.86,0:09:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They pour themselves out for the friends, \Nthus identifying themselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as disciples of Christ.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.00,0:09:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do not have \Nto be an elder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide a word \Nof encouragement, do we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If we all keep focused \Non others in the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.25,0:09:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,not just ourselves, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we will know \Nwho needs to be bolstered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.72,0:09:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because of trials \Nor circumstances that they face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.52,0:09:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving in this way \Nis evidence of Christlike love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.53,0:09:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be thinking, \N‘But I’m just a little old sister \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘who finds it hard to squeeze out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.60,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a word of encouragement to others.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.17,0:09:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you don’t have \Nto say anything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.74,0:09:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,just be there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.14,0:09:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at the meetings \Nor in the service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.14,0:09:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When others see your face, \Nthey are encouraged. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:10:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow along \Nas I read Acts 28:15. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It reads: \N“From there the brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“when they heard the news about us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“came as far \Nas the Marketplace of Appius \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.19,0:10:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“and Three Taverns to meet us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.53,0:10:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“On catching sight of them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Paul thanked God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and took courage.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.64,0:10:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul “took courage” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.01,0:10:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just by seeing the brothers \Nwho came out to meet him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You encourage your brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and sisters by your presence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please follow along as I read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.99,0:10:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians 2:1-4. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul here describes it \Nas “encouragement in Christ.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.26,0:10:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“If, then, there is \Nany encouragement in Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“if any consolation of love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.64,0:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“if any spiritual fellowship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:11:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“if any tender affection \Nand compassion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“make my joy full by being \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the same mind \Nand having the same love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“being completely united, \Nhaving the one thought in mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do nothing out of contentiousness \Nor out of egotism, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“but with humility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.66,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“consider others superior to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“as you look out not only \Nfor your own interests, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but also for the interests of others.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.21,0:11:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nthe self-sacrificing aspect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of this love and encouragement? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.98,0:11:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he talked about having love, \Nbut then he said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“not . . . for your own interests, \Nbut . . . for the interests of others.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That type of love\N—in the interests of others—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.16,0:11:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is the identifying mark \Nof true Christians.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.53,0:11:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What about visiting \Nthe sick in your congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.33,0:11:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or those who are housebound? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:12:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes these dear ones are \N“out of sight, out of mind.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We visit with those we see \Nwhen at the Kingdom Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but do we think about those \Nwho are shut-ins? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What was a major part \Nof Jesus’ loving acts when on earth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There are numerous accounts \Nof Jesus and his apostles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.02,0:12:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,healing the sick. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.02,0:12:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that we \Ncannot heal the sick, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.43,0:12:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is in our power \Nto visit the sick. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a healing \Nthat is to their spirit! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It means so much when \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.44,0:12:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not just prayed for \Nat a meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.04,0:12:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but when those words of prayer \Nare backed up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with an act of love\N—a visit to them in person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That is Christlike love in action. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.45,0:12:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not scroll down the list \Nof those in your service group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.19,0:12:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with the thought in mind \Nof checking on those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:12:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been missing \Nfrom the meetings? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they need a meal? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.83,0:13:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they need some help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.27,0:13:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps around the house? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.27,0:13:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they need transportation \Nto the doctor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.61,0:13:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we allow our love \Nto expand to fill their needs?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.61,0:13:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Contributing to the worldwide work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which cares for the needs \Nof our brothers around the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is another act of love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It demonstrates that we are \Na true disciple of Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.89,0:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Related to that, many of you have, \Nat your own expense, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled to far-flung places \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.43,0:13:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to help rebuild \Nafter a natural disaster has struck. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.27,0:13:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The overwhelming response \Nfrom the victims is evidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.74,0:13:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of your self-sacrificing life \Nand love for your brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.08,0:13:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is hoped \Nthat the reminder of Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at John 13:34, 35 \Nwill be good for all of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:13:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not just for this month, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but for our whole course of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.66,0:14:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, about one third \Nof the world’s population \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.53,0:14:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,claims to be Christian. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But how many of them \Nshow self-sacrificing love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of their immediate family? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.30,0:14:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Most are like a baseball team \Nin a uniform. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They think having the word “Christian” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.31,0:14:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,emblazoned across the front \Nof their uniform \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.41,0:14:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is all that is required. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.85,0:14:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, most of them \Nsimply “sit on the bench,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or on a pew in church, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.25,0:14:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and many do not even attend \N“the game.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not live \Nthe life of a Christian. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus made clear \Nthat being a true disciple of his \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.50,0:14:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is not merely \N“wearing a uniform,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.60,0:14:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,simply claiming to be \Nhis follower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it involves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.57,0:14:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,actively demonstrating \Nworks of love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.34,0:14:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“swinging hard for the team,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.95,0:15:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,imitating the all-time greatest examples \Nof love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.18,0:15:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah God and his Son, \NJesus Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As Paul said \Nat 2 Corinthians 8:8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we need “to test \Nthe genuineness of [our] love.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.93,0:15:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we need to daily prove \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.86,0:15:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are \Na genuine disciple of Jesus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.87,0:15:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Reinmueller will now \Nshare some examples of how \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.01,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible principles \Nwe just discussed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.24,0:15:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have helped people \Naround the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.38,0:15:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Herd, \Nfor that warm encouragement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re more motivated than ever \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to prove our love for Jehovah and others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.82,0:15:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We recently met Mamuka Tektumanashvili, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.02,0:15:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from the country of Georgia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.66,0:15:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a high-ranking officer \Nin the special forces there for many years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.60,0:15:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What made him realize \Nthat defending his country \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the highest honor \Na man can have in his life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is his story.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For 18 years \NI served in a special unit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.40,0:16:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible \Nfor presidential security. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.93,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This mission \Ndemanded total self-sacrifice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nthe first and the last vehicles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.61,0:16:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presidential escort \Nbelonged to this unit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So if an attack \Noccurred on the president, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.54,0:16:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we were the first ones \Nto be hit with the fire.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last ten years \Nof service, I worked \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.95,0:16:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as an instructor \Nand trained new staff \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide \Npresidential security in the future. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.43,0:16:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Those working in this field \Nmust be fearless. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They must be professionals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is what I taught \Nto succeeding generations.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I just loved my job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.31,0:17:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a fervent patriot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.64,0:17:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a special regard \Nfor the flag of my country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.95,0:17:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In one bag, \NI always had weapons and the flag. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.29,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Patriotism \Nwas so deep-rooted in me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I would beat up a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.36,0:17:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,simply because he was \Nof another nationality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought \Nthat God would never allow\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,people like me \Nto draw close to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.07,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, Jehovah’s Witnesses came \Nand preached to my wife and me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We were so interested \Nin the truth that my wife\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.84,0:17:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,even expressed \Na desire to study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.44,0:17:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there were rumors \Ncirculating about Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.71,0:17:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided first to make sure that everything\Nwas decent at their meetings\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.65,0:17:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and only then allow my wife \Nto associate with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.98,0:17:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,After the meeting, \NI was absolutely thrilled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.99,0:17:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was well-mannered, \Nwith friendly, smiling faces. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.99,0:17:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that there was nothing there \Nto threaten my wife’s well-being. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, their association \Nwould be beneficial for her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.27,0:18:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon my wife \Nand our eldest daughter got baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As for me, I enjoyed associating \Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.54,0:18:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, I also started \Nto study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.28,0:18:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that I had to make \Ndrastic changes in my life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.68,0:18:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but my job \Nprevented me from doing so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, I felt \Nthat door-to-door preaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.09,0:18:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was far more difficult \Nthan engaging in combat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I respected Jehovah’s Witnesses \Nfor their courage and strength.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Little by little, \NI too was changing for the better. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.76,0:18:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to quit my job and inform \Nmy colleagues about my religious beliefs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.70,0:18:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wrote down all the Bible verses \NI had recently learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then pinned them \Non the wall in my office.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.75,0:18:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I also started to think \Nabout how to make a living \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,after leaving my job \Nand decided to learn a trade. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to buy tools \Nin order to be ready \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to take care of my family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.42,0:19:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that the time \Nhad come to make a decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.83,0:19:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The day I quit my job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was one of the happiest days \Nof my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.23,0:19:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I’ve been able \Nto dedicate every minute of my life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah \Nwith a clean conscience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In a few months, I got baptized.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.24,0:19:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, \Nwe were hardly making a living. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.45,0:19:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this taught me \Nto trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.25,0:19:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to keep \Nservice to Jehovah in first place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I deeply appreciate \Nthe support of my brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and sisters \Nand association with them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.40,0:19:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, I used to carry out \Nthe orders of men\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—some of which \NI carried out reluctantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.51,0:19:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I am happy to carry out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:19:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an assignment from Jehovah \Nwith the same spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.98,0:20:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that the prophet Isaiah had, \Nwho said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.45,0:20:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! Send me!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As a family, we decided to move \Nwhere the need was greater, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.56,0:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and this has united \Nour family even more.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.99,0:20:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the bag \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in which \NI always carried weapons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but now they are replaced \Nwith a Bible and Bible literature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.17,0:20:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, I thought \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never preach \Nfrom door to door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.17,0:20:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I can say with conviction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.27,0:20:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that the words of Jesus \Nhave proved true in my case: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.41,0:20:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“All things are possible with God.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Tektumanashvili \Nnow serves as an elder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.69,0:20:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has also been \Na regular pioneer since 2014.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.13,0:20:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,While Brother Tektumanashvili \Nserved the government for many years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.26,0:20:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there are those who live \Non the other side of the law. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah’s unprejudiced love \Nreach out to them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.41,0:20:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Join us as we travel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.54,0:21:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Democratic Republic of Congo \Nin Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.68,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,where our brothers make \Nspecial efforts to reach people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.01,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we would not normally \Nfind from door to door.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.52,0:21:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I could say that my past \Nwas really an unhappy past. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.19,0:21:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through very difficult times \Nduring my childhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.67,0:21:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost hope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.67,0:21:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could ever have \Na better life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.41,0:21:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to associate \Nwith the wrong people in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.08,0:21:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One night, I was arrested \Nand sent to Buluo Prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.35,0:21:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a high-security prison \Nin Congo.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.29,0:21:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Prison is a very dangerous place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:21:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was surprised how they \Naccepted the truth so easily. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:21:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I was amazed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.27,0:22:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We needed to obtain permission \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to continue \Nto preach in the prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We had so enjoyed \Nthe preaching work there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to see the authorities in the city \Nto find out what was required \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could have permission \Nto preach in the prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To my great amazement, \Nthey simply handed me a paper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.13,0:22:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and told me to put \Nmy request in writing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.10,0:22:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked me to wait. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.10,0:22:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Within minutes, \NI had the authorization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.07,0:22:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in my hands \Nwithout paying anything at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.10,0:22:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time the situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.27,0:22:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seemed insurmountable to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.57,0:22:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.64,0:22:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw the hand of Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.65,0:22:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,providing us \Nwith the suitable solution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The authorization gave a great boost \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to this special witnessing initiative. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.69,0:22:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In harmony with 1 Corinthians 9:22, 23, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.56,0:23:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers could then \N‘become all things to people of all sorts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.83,0:23:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they might \Nby all possible means save some.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.04,0:23:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Some religious leaders \Nwho were also prisoners \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.11,0:23:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,were extremely opposed \Nto our presence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.34,0:23:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They conspired and had us \Nthrown out of our meeting place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.32,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The prisoners themselves \Nwere concerned about this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They found another meeting place \Neven more spacious than the former.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Buluo is eight kilometers \Naway from our congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to transport the group who support \Nthe preaching work and meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.27,0:23:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the body of elders organized two minibuses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.67,0:23:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to go out every Saturday to Buluo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.48,0:23:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Once they arrive, \Nthey begin the preaching work at 8:30, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and at 10 o’clock \Nthe meetings start. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.72,0:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All the meetings of the week \Nare held on the Saturday.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.99,0:24:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Concerning Jehovah’s Witnesses, \Npersonally, I am very impressed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.16,0:24:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s more than three years they’ve been \Nmore active in helping the detainees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.97,0:24:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The reeducation of the prisoners \Nis assured by Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.97,0:24:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good collaboration \Non the part of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.64,0:24:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With this I’m very happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.65,0:24:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One hundred \Nand seventy-five attended \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.82,0:24:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the circuit assembly \Nin December 2014, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.22,0:24:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which was held in the prison, \Nand seven were baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.19,0:24:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Local media covered the event.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.27,0:24:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I have seen \NJehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,baptized here \Nin the Buluo Prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.94,0:24:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.94,0:24:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I encourage you \Nto continue with this assistance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.01,0:24:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Every week there are \Nmore than 80 in attendance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.38,0:25:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes \Nmore than that, even 140. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.28,0:25:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the attendance \Nthere are the 36 publishers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.32,0:25:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—the brothers who learned \Nthe truth in Buluo Prison—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.12,0:25:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,30 are baptized \Nand 6 unbaptized.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.06,0:25:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I visited many churches \Nbecause I had a lot of questions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.77,0:25:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never got \Nany exact answers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.67,0:25:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went to see \NJehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.51,0:25:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they gave me accurate answers \Nfrom the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.41,0:25:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To know that Jehovah \Nis compassionate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.48,0:25:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and ready to forgive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.48,0:25:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the qualities \Nthat touched me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.56,0:25:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be a soldier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.89,0:25:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the military. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.89,0:25:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I attended various churches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.23,0:25:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because I had a question \Nthat bothered me a lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.73,0:25:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered why God allows \Nbad things to happen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.90,0:25:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to people all the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.71,0:26:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While I was in prison, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.58,0:26:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses came to visit \Nand talk to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.28,0:26:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked them \Nthe same question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.82,0:26:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why does God allow sickness \Nand suffering to continue?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.29,0:26:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They replied by using \Nthree Bible verses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.63,0:26:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very happy because I received \Nthe answer to my question.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.70,0:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Papy Okito is a brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who learned \Nthe truth in prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.71,0:26:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He made \Nsuch remarkable progress \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.41,0:26:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that those in charge \Nnow have confidence in him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.15,0:26:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Joseph in the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.29,0:26:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he has been placed in a position \Nof supervision over the other prisoners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.76,0:26:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He also made further progress, \Nand thus, the management has requested \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.09,0:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that his prison sentence \Nbe reduced.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.70,0:26:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived in the prison, \NI had lost hope. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.57,0:27:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought for me \Nit was the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.60,0:27:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.61,0:27:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have found joy \Nand hope in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.88,0:27:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why today I am happy \Neven though I am still here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.75,0:27:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know \Nthat the Paradise is for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.43,0:27:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been five years \Nsince the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.27,0:27:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,started preaching \Nin the Buluo Prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.57,0:27:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, the publishers place \Nup to 500 magazines in one weekend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.34,0:27:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Although our success is not \Nmeasured by the number of placements, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.25,0:27:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this response does paint \Na clear picture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.75,0:27:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the spiritual thirst \Namong these prisoners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.72,0:27:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last few months, \Ninside these prison walls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.19,0:27:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,11 more unbaptized publishers \Nhave been approved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.96,0:28:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What a loving act by Jehovah \Nand his organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.26,0:28:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to help such individuals satisfy \Ntheir spiritual needs!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.40,0:28:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 1950’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.04,0:28:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the opposition \Nagainst Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.34,0:28:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the former Soviet Union \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.34,0:28:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in homes being searched, \Nbrothers being followed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.98,0:28:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of our brothers \Nand sisters being sent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.55,0:28:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to Communist concentration camps \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.55,0:28:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in Siberia, \Namong other places. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.09,0:28:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1956 and 1957, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.76,0:28:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,over 462,000 \Nconvention delegates worldwide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.53,0:28:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,unanimously adopted a petition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.20,0:28:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which clearly outlined the treatment \NJehovah’s Witnesses were enduring. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.13,0:28:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was sent \Nto the Soviet authorities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.97,0:28:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but sadly, not much changed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.04,0:28:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The next year, \Nat the 1958 international convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.88,0:28:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at Yankee Stadium \Nin New York, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.88,0:28:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a talk was given entitled \N“Behind the Iron Curtain.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,During the talk, \Ndelegates were surprised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.09,0:29:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when a recording of greetings \Nand songs from brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.46,0:29:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and sisters in the Soviet Union \Nwas played. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.16,0:29:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the risk of losing \Ntheir freedom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.16,0:29:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers produced \Nand sent these recordings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.40,0:29:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a few months ago, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,some of those who were involved \Nin making the recording \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.60,0:29:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,were able to listen to it \Nfor the first time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.57,0:29:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Several of them \Nfound out only then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.58,0:29:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that the recording had been played \Nat the convention at Yankee Stadium. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.25,0:29:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our team was present \Nat that gathering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.90,0:29:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers told us \Nto prepare songs for a recording.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.44,0:29:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were singing, \NI never imagined \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.97,0:29:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was for a convention, \Nbecause I did not know about that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.14,0:29:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We sang as usual.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.15,0:30:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The chorus was made up \Nof about 20 persons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.85,0:30:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the recording \Nwas made in a room \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.82,0:30:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a barrack-like building.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.63,0:30:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I just looked after the chorus \Nto give them the right tone.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.63,0:30:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone sang a little off-key, \Nshe would right away remark: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.97,0:30:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Altos, you are off!” \Nor “Tenor, you are off!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.31,0:30:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that there would be no slips, \Nno mistakes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.05,0:30:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to be very careful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.45,0:30:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were recording.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.29,0:30:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we knew not to talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.45,0:30:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not tell \Nanyone about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.52,0:30:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was secret\N—absolutely secret.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.60,0:30:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They chose a brother \Nwho spoke very good Russian, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.07,0:30:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who had good intonation, \Nand who had a good voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.24,0:31:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I recall, we made \Nthe recording on our first attempt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.61,0:31:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Yuriy Dobychin \Nsaid the greetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.35,0:31:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was young then, \Nand I had a good voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.76,0:31:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to say \Nthe greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.76,0:31:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from the brothers \Nin the Soviet Union \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.20,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the brothers gathered \Nat Yankee Stadium.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.81,0:31:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As the brothers who made \Nthe recording told me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.81,0:31:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the most difficult assignment \Nfor them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.02,0:31:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was how to get this recording \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.29,0:31:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,across the border. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.52,0:31:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers cut it up \Ninto pieces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.46,0:31:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and sewed it \Ninto the lining of a jacket \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.19,0:31:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because that’s how \Nconfidential letters were sent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.63,0:32:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One married couple \Nfrom Poland, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.84,0:32:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who were vacationing \Nin Russia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.84,0:32:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,agreed to take it \Nback with them\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.11,0:32:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—to take it \Nout of the Soviet Union. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.14,0:32:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s where they ran \Ninto serious problems.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.65,0:32:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,From Brother Scheider’s letter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.69,0:32:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who received \Nthe audio recording in Poland: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.96,0:32:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The security officers separated \Nour brother from the others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.36,0:32:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then an officer said to him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.70,0:32:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Please give us the film \Nand the three letters you have with you.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.90,0:32:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“The brother saw now, \Nof course, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“that there had been \Na traitor somewhere. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.31,0:32:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“He and his wife \Nwere now thoroughly searched. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.44,0:32:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“Every square centimeter \Nof their cases \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.01,0:32:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“was carefully examined \Ntogether with their contents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.48,0:32:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then both were stripped naked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.99,0:32:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“While this was going on, \Nthey yelled at the brother: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.46,0:32:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Tell us where you have hidden everything \Nor to whom you have given it!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.73,0:33:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“They were absolutely convinced \Nthat he had everything with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.43,0:33:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Several times they took him \Nto the office \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.47,0:33:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the frontier police \Nand to the security police, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.27,0:33:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“searching him \Nagain and again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.64,0:33:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and being terribly angry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.78,0:33:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“But they finally had to give up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“They kept him back \Nfor 24 hours \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.48,0:33:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“and questioned him \Nin the presence of ten specialists. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.25,0:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But he came out victorious.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.76,0:33:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, even the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.59,0:33:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who were involved \Ndon’t know who this couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.96,0:33:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who brought the tape \Ninto Poland was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.17,0:35:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for me it was, of course, a great joy, \Nsince the goal was reached after all.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.38,0:35:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was so wonderful \Nat that time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.38,0:35:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I really enjoyed it all!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.38,0:35:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing could describe \Nthe joy I felt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.85,0:35:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was overwhelmed with feelings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.86,0:35:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so my voice was recorded, \Nand the greetings were heard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.87,0:35:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in New York \Nat Yankee Stadium.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.32,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These dear brothers and sisters \Nhave no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.46,0:36:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They are happy \Nthat their efforts encouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.83,0:36:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so many thousands \Nback then and today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.90,0:36:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of love \Nthese brothers and sisters showed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.13,0:36:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is often noticed \Nby those not in the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.80,0:36:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A young couple from the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.34,0:36:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah and Holly Draper, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.71,0:36:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced just that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.68,0:36:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The blessings that I enjoy today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.35,0:36:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,are so numerous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.79,0:36:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a true inner sense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.39,0:36:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of joy and happiness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.99,0:36:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t help \Nbut be appreciative, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.20,0:36:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so grateful \Nfor all that Jehovah does.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.23,0:37:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t \Nalways this way for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.92,0:37:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a dark world growing up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.59,0:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I never knew \Nwhat being a child was like. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.63,0:37:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.77,0:37:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of who I would grow up to be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.40,0:37:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I had no choice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.61,0:37:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at a very young age, \NI, as well, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.58,0:37:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,started to partake \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.51,0:37:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I saw going on around me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.78,0:37:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned quickly that it helped numb \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.05,0:37:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the feelings that I had. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.02,0:37:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Drugs were a way \Nto escape that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.36,0:37:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a lot of trouble \Nwith the law. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.09,0:37:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I needed change, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.76,0:38:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so I joined the military \Nat a young age.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.00,0:38:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Around my teenage years, \Nmy life became difficult. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.77,0:38:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to turn to drugs and alcohol \Nand self-destructive ways, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but none of these things \Nwere making me happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.11,0:38:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very lonely. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.61,0:38:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No one knew me; \Nno one cared to know me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.65,0:38:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt so lost, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.95,0:38:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was trying \Nto fill this big hole in my heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.42,0:38:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with so many things,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.23,0:38:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and none of it worked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.83,0:38:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my many car accidents, \Ndue to drugs and alcohol, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.50,0:38:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ended me up in jail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.64,0:38:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for 30 days straight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.64,0:38:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like a hopeless mess. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.18,0:38:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just knew \Nsomething’s got to change. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.69,0:38:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I joined the military, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.75,0:39:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking it was going to be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.82,0:39:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the positive great change \Nthat I needed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.19,0:39:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was not.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.96,0:39:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember \Njoining the military \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.27,0:39:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping that it \Nwould bring some sort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.27,0:39:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of authority into my life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.27,0:39:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but I again started \Nto spiral \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.71,0:39:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,into my anger,\Nmy alcohol and drug abuse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.94,0:39:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The military decided \Nto let me out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.22,0:39:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But during deployment \Nis where I met Holly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.22,0:39:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Holly also got \Nout of the military, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.82,0:39:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and we started \Nto live a life together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.46,0:39:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But we were still searching \Nfor something to fill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.70,0:39:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the emptiness \Nthat we both felt in our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.40,0:39:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah and I were both working \Nin a steel factory in Montana. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.34,0:39:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,During this time, \NI was being trained on a drill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.01,0:39:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by one of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \Na sister named Molly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.55,0:39:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Molly said, “You’re \Ngoing to have down time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.98,0:40:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“on this machine, \Nmaybe a couple of hours, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so feel free to read \Nwhatever I have in my tool box.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.09,0:40:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I opened it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.09,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and immediately \Na little yellow book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What Does the Bible Really Teach?, \Ncaught my eye. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.16,0:40:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved the pictures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.13,0:40:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The scriptures \Nat the beginning of the book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.50,0:40:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,they touched my heart immediately, \Nand I felt like, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.24,0:40:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‘These answer all the questions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.94,0:40:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been searching \Nfor my entire life!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.54,0:40:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Another sister came over, \Nher name was Cory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.74,0:40:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said:\N“Molly and I can come over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.98,0:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“and we can talk to you \Nabout the Bible tomorrow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.42,0:40:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have any questions, \Nwe’d love to answer them using the Bible.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.02,0:40:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Yes, come over!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.29,0:40:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a little bit \Nmore apprehensive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.46,0:40:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I stayed just to make sure \Nnothing got weird, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.76,0:40:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but this was finally \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.76,0:40:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,something very different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.76,0:40:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized what they were saying \Ncame from the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.53,0:40:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d never seen that before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.70,0:40:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They invited us \Nto the Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.14,0:41:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We went in, \Neverybody had their Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.48,0:41:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,had time to look \Nthe scriptures up together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.91,0:41:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody was \Nso warm and inviting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.75,0:41:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,These were the people \NI’d been searching for my entire life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.62,0:41:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden change \Nwas possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.65,0:41:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew what changes \Nwe needed to make in our life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.46,0:41:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What we were doing, \Nour actions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.66,0:41:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we had to clear out things \Nthat Jehovah hates.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.06,0:41:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like just going through \Nour house and deciding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.06,0:41:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is \Nthat we need to get rid of. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.13,0:41:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,By allowing the truth \Nto transform our lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.80,0:41:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Holly and I’ve received \Nmany blessings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.07,0:41:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually we were able \Nto come here together and serve at Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.61,0:41:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the truth in a weld shop, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.25,0:41:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I get to weld \Nhere in Jehovah’s house for him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.52,0:41:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I perform maintenance \Non water fountains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.75,0:41:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,refrigerators, coolers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.49,0:41:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Being trained by the brothers \Nand sisters I work with \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.59,0:41:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just helps me to refine \Nmy Christian personality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.36,0:41:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so nice to know \Nthat Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.10,0:41:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking down on us; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.37,0:42:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was able \Nto see through \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.73,0:42:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the trash \Nthat was there in our life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.24,0:42:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He was able to find something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.27,0:42:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to work with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.27,0:42:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really think of a scripture, \NPsalm 145:19: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.91,0:42:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“He satisfies the desire \Nof those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.15,0:42:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“who fear him; \Nhe hears their [cry] for help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.62,0:42:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and [he] rescues them.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.06,0:42:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah did that for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.89,0:42:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask Jehovah \Nto display his hand in your life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.39,0:42:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,no doubt at all in my mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.13,0:42:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that will happen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.54,0:42:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how \NJeremiah and Holly were touched \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Christian love shown to them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.24,0:42:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when they visited \Nthe Kingdom Hall for the first time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.08,0:42:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah said that everybody \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.45,0:42:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was so warm and inviting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.82,0:42:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, love truly is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.52,0:42:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the identifying mark of Jesus’ disciples.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.75,0:42:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus taught that love \Nfor fellow believers and our neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.32,0:43:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is second to our love for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.09,0:43:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Being kind and encouraging to others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.46,0:43:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is of little value if it’s not rooted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.27,0:43:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in a deep desire \Nto please our heavenly Father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.64,0:43:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.37,0:43:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a young brother is reminded of the value \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.94,0:43:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of carefully examining his heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.96,0:43:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Shawn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.96,0:43:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised in the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.33,0:43:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing everything right.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.51,0:43:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was doing everything wrong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.91,0:44:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in my senior year of high school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.11,0:44:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was going great \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.18,0:44:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until this new girl joined our school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.42,0:44:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don’t know \Nhow it even started. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.76,0:44:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We just sort of hit it off \Nand became good friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.20,0:44:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, she was so easy to talk to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.89,0:45:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.89,0:45:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we were texting all the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.63,0:45:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one thing led to another.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.47,0:45:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, when things \Nstarted to get physical, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.34,0:45:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I could control it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.14,0:45:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was only getting worse.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.79,0:45:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to let my parents down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.26,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started lying to them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.66,0:45:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I started lying to myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.14,0:46:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought if I could just keep \Ngoing to the meetings and do my parts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.81,0:46:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it could somehow be OK.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.21,0:46:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was far from OK.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.09,0:46:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The next night, we had family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.83,0:46:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We were reading about the account \Nof Ananias and his wife, Sapphira. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.37,0:46:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When a special fund was set up \Nfor needy Christians, Ananias sold a field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.37,0:46:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, he boldly claimed \Nhe was contributing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.31,0:46:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire proceeds of its sale. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.62,0:46:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, though, \NAnanias had “secretly held back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.49,0:46:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the price” \Nfor his personal gain.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.32,0:46:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter boldly said to him: \N“You have lied, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.36,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not to men, but to God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.93,0:47:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wasn’t fooled \Nby their pretense. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.24,0:47:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we read Psalm 44:21: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.24,0:47:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“[God] is aware \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.25,0:47:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the secrets of the heart.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.99,0:47:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading this account of Ananias \Nand Sapphira made me realize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.10,0:47:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t just lying \Nto my parents or my friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.94,0:47:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was lying to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.58,0:47:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As much as I didn’t want \Nto let my parents down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.72,0:47:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,even more so, \NI didn’t want to let Jehovah down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.26,0:48:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed long that night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.00,0:48:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t hold anything back.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.68,0:48:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By the next morning, \NI knew what I wanted to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.21,0:48:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t easy, \Nbut my parents were very supportive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.95,0:48:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I also got the help \NI needed from the elders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.57,0:49:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a few years, \Nbut as I look back now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.90,0:49:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of those kids \Nliving a double life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.58,0:49:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But now with Jehovah’s help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.38,0:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m living the best life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.59,0:49:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What a clear warning this is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.09,0:49:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not only for young ones \Nbut also for those of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.56,0:49:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,who have served Jehovah \Nfor many, many years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.53,0:49:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As we well know, serving Jehovah \Nfaithfully for many decades \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.17,0:49:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is only valuable \Nif we ‘endure to the end.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.84,0:49:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By developing \Nintense love for Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.31,0:49:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll be able to overcome \Nwhatever temptations or trials we face.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.88,0:50:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking \Nof enduring to the end, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.58,0:50:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mark Sanderson recently spoke \Nat morning worship in Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.69,0:50:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about how our eager expectation \Nof the day of Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.59,0:50:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us to endure faithfully \Nin this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.29,0:50:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay close attention \Nto some of the ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.40,0:50:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we show such expectation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.90,0:50:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here’s the question \Nwe want to ask this morning: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.37,0:50:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it actually possible \Nto speed up the day of Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.17,0:50:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we look at our text this morning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.84,0:50:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Peter 3:11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.68,0:50:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve had that read for us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.85,0:50:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,so we know \Nthat expression at the end \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.49,0:50:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that we should “consider \Nwhat sort of people you ought to be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.22,0:50:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in holy acts of conduct \Nand deeds of godly devotion.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.39,0:50:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But then it goes on to say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.66,0:50:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“As you await and keep close in mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.23,0:50:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of the day of Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.37,0:50:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, if you look at the footnote \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.94,0:51:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on this expression in verse 12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.24,0:51:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll notice that the expression \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.78,0:51:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“keep close in mind” literally means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.48,0:51:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to “speed up” the day of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.28,0:51:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, how can we do that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.65,0:51:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s true we cannot bring \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.39,0:51:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the day forward of Jehovah \Neven one day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.46,0:51:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,nor can we move it \Nback even one day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.69,0:51:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not within our power. \NThat day is set. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.03,0:51:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can we, then, \N“speed up” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.97,0:51:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the day of Jehovah \Nas it says there in verse 12? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.20,0:51:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we keep that day \Nclose in our mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.44,0:51:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We never let it be out of our sight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.11,0:51:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As the footnote also says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.15,0:51:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we “eagerly desire” it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.08,0:51:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, \Nif we’re persons like that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.65,0:51:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter says \Nthat we’re going to be busy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.22,0:51:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in “deeds of godly devotion.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.73,0:51:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, \Njust as a quick reminder: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.79,0:51:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is godly devotion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.83,0:51:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just looking \Nat our New World Translation glossary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.73,0:52:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,here’s the definition: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.74,0:52:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s “reverence, worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.77,0:52:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“and service to Jehovah God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.07,0:52:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with loyalty \Nto his universal sovereignty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.11,0:52:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do we get \Nfrom that definition? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.78,0:52:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\N—reverence, worship, service? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.82,0:52:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, godly devotion \Nis not passive; it’s active. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.39,0:52:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s reflected \Nin action and in activity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.66,0:52:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s why the apostle Peter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.06,0:52:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,used the expression in verse 11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.20,0:52:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“deeds of godly devotion.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.17,0:52:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what are some of the ways \Nthat we demonstrate this quality? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.04,0:52:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some of them are just very small. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.47,0:52:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, what about hospitality? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.41,0:52:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Peter 4:9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.08,0:52:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when the apostle Peter \Nwrote his first letter, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.48,0:52:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be hospitable \Nto one another without grumbling.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.72,0:52:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are \Nso many opportunities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.86,0:53:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to imitate Jehovah \Nand be hospitable\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.96,0:53:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—to share with others \Naccording to their needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.56,0:53:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And this really is an expression \Nnot only for another person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.67,0:53:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s an expression \Nof our love for Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.71,0:53:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—our desire to want \Nto imitate him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.87,0:53:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we all acknowledge that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.88,0:53:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s the question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.98,0:53:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the last time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.45,0:53:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you acted hospitably? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.72,0:53:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Or when was the last time \NI acted hospitably? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.62,0:53:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it’s not enough just to love \Nthe quality of hospitality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.82,0:53:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are going \Nto have deeds of godly devotion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.73,0:53:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to have to practice it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.73,0:53:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s another one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.73,0:53:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What about helping the elderly \Nthat are in our midst? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.04,0:53:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nour elderly brothers need help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.84,0:53:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They need help \Nto get to the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.07,0:53:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They need help \Nto get out in the field ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.08,0:53:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them \Nare confined to their homes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.81,0:53:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that’s the case, \Nthey may need help from younger ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.15,0:54:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to assist them \Nwith shopping or doing errands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.29,0:54:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or just doing \Nsome chore around the house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.99,0:54:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s something \Nthat has been mentioned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.69,0:54:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in many Watchtower articles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.00,0:54:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been mentioned \Nat many conventions and assemblies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.00,0:54:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been mentioned \Nat many congregation meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.04,0:54:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s a question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.04,0:54:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the last time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.24,0:54:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that you did something \Nfor an elderly brother or sister? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.08,0:54:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Or when was the last time I did? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.08,0:54:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we need to think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.35,0:54:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about not just loving these ideas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.32,0:54:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but what are we doing to really help? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.79,0:54:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that’s showing \Ndeeds of godly devotion.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.66,0:54:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, we also have to think \Nabout the more major things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.86,0:54:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What about attending \Nour congregation meetings? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.16,0:54:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 10:23-25\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.43,0:54:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—that scripture \Nthat we quote so many times—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.47,0:54:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,says that we should ‘not forsake \Nour meeting together.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.64,0:54:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But it goes on to say \Nthat we should ‘encourage one another.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.61,0:55:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s not enough \Njust to be at the meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.58,0:55:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re there, we want to reach out \Nand do everything that we can \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.45,0:55:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage our brothers \Nand really participate in the meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.46,0:55:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, godly devotion \Nis not passive; it’s active. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.16,0:55:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, what sort of persons ought we to be \Nwhen we’re at the meeting? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.53,0:55:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know we want to be active, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.47,0:55:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,fully involved with the program.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.27,0:55:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, of course, \Nwhat’s the most important way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.44,0:55:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that we exercise \Nthese deeds of godly devotion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.41,0:55:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you’ll remember \Nthat the apostle Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.98,0:55:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Timothy 3:16 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.58,0:55:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,referred to ‘the sacred secret \Nof godly devotion,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.92,0:55:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and he showed there \Nthat Jesus really was that secret. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.36,0:55:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he was \Nthe one who demonstrated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,godly devotion \Nin a perfect sense. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.63,0:55:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Paul in that verse, \N1 Timothy 3:16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.60,0:56:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,went on to say that Jesus \Nwas ‘preached among the nations.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.37,0:56:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then, that really is \Na vital part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.84,0:56:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of our deeds of godly devotion\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.98,0:56:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,—preaching about Christ Jesus, \Nhis Kingdom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.48,0:56:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything \Nthat will be accomplished. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.99,0:56:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But brothers, \Nhow much incentive we have today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.22,0:56:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be involved fully \Nin our preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.53,0:56:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We have tools today \Nlike we have never had before.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.80,0:56:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, over the summer \Nas I was attending \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.77,0:56:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of different regional conventions \Nin different parts of the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.57,0:56:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoyed so much, \Nno doubt just as you have, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.24,0:56:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,using the JW Library app \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.95,0:56:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and downloading \Nthe Why Study the Bible? video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.35,0:56:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in a number of different languages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.85,0:56:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We had one real interesting experience \Nwhen we were in Europe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.15,0:56:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We got into a taxi \Nwith a driver from Africa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.63,0:56:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And right away, \Nwe asked him what his language was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.33,0:56:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he told us it was \Na language not familiar to us at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.97,0:57:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But while he was driving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.27,0:57:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we managed to download \Nthe Why Study the Bible? video, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.54,0:57:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it automatically \Nbegan to play as we were in the car. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.38,0:57:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as soon as the man heard it, \Nhe started shouting: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.15,0:57:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“What’s happening? \NWhat’s happening?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.18,0:57:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he thought \Nhe was hearing a voice from heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.02,0:57:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when he heard \Nhis own language in the taxi. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.05,0:57:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But we reassured him \Nthat that was not the case. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.39,0:57:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was so moved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.59,0:57:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He almost didn’t want to take the fare, \Nif you can imagine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.53,0:57:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and initially \Nhe had been quite unfriendly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.30,0:57:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he saw \Nwhat was available on our website, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.44,0:57:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he was deeply moved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.44,0:57:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe \Nyou’ve had a similar experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.11,0:57:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as a note of future reference: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.18,0:57:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s probably not a good idea \Nto play the video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.25,0:57:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when someone is driving.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.45,0:57:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we have \Nreal godly devotion that’s active, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.39,0:57:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to be busy \Nin doing deeds of godly devotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.99,0:57:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nthere’s an old saying that says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.33,0:58:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Time flies when you’re having fun.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.53,0:58:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, even scientists \Nacknowledge that there’s truth in that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.87,0:58:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A study that was published \Nin the year 2012 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.54,0:58:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in the journal \NPsychological Science said this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.74,0:58:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we tend to believe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.98,0:58:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that time flies \Nwhen we’re having a good time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.01,0:58:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these studies \Nindicate that what it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.72,0:58:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about the enjoyable time \Nthat causes it to go by more quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.92,0:58:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be the goal pursuit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.39,0:58:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or achievement-directed action \Nwe’re engaged in that matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.03,0:58:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being content or satisfied \Nmay not make time fly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.97,0:58:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but being excited or actively pursuing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.77,0:58:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a desired object can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.77,0:58:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that interesting?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.78,0:58:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, if we’re \Nthe sort of persons that are busy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.58,0:58:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with holy acts of conduct \Nand deeds of godly devotion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.65,0:59:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching out for that most important goal \Nof everlasting life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.35,0:59:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we will speed up the coming \Nof the day of Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.56,0:59:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in our hearts and our minds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.96,0:59:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What deeds of godly devotion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,do you remember \Nfrom that fine presentation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.63,0:59:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Among other things, \NBrother Sanderson explained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.77,0:59:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that one deed of godly devotion \Nis to be hospitable to one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.61,0:59:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospitality is also the theme \Nof this month’s music video, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.68,0:59:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is entitled \N“Follow the Course [of Hospitality].”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.66,0:59:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be a meal or snacks or coffee\NOr fun and games, maybe just talking.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.68,1:00:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is the one who put it on our table.\NSo could we be able . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.09,1:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the course of hospitality.”\NImitate God above.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.50,1:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it with true impartiality.\NThat’s what it means to love.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.28,1:00:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The roof above our heads \Nis from our heavenly Father.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.73,1:00:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we need to share, \Nwould it be a bother?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.17,1:01:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s feel the joy \Nthat only ever comes from giving!\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.44,1:01:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Christian living.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.58,1:01:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the course of hospitality.”\NImitate God above.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.19,1:01:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it with true impartiality.\NThat’s what it means to love.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.81,1:01:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people don’t have what we have.\NIt’s up to us to share.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.15,1:01:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Disaster strikes, then they’re without.\NWill we really care?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.29,1:02:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we open up our home \Nand host a friend in need?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.30,1:02:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do a kindly deed.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.67,1:02:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the course of hospitality.”\NImitate God above.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.02,1:02:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it with true impartiality.\NThat’s what it means to love.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.03,1:02:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what it means to love.\NThat’s what it means to love.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.30,1:02:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice song! \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.30,1:02:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And while that music video \Nbrings this program to its conclusion, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.21,1:02:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d like to encourage you to watch a video \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.41,1:02:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be posted later this month \Nabout Sister Cindy McIntosh. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.75,1:02:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She was in the military for many years \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.65,1:02:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and described herself as having become \Na “dark and uncaring person.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.25,1:02:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Jehovah taught her \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.22,1:03:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what true love means. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.03,1:03:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The video is entitled I Put Down My Rifle \Nand is available on Video on Demand \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.93,1:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the “Interviews \Nand Experiences” category.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.00,1:03:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, love truly is \Nthe identifying mark of true Christians. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.67,1:03:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what stands out \Nwhen you \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.97,1:03:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,visit other congregations, \Nperhaps when traveling. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.98,1:03:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One good example \Nis the Nong Khai Congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.01,1:03:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the northeastern corner of Thailand. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.28,1:03:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The 32 publishers send their love.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.39,1:03:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a great need in Thailand, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.02,1:03:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which is why half \Nof the 10 appointed brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.89,1:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation \Nand half of the 18 pioneers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.30,1:03:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are “need greaters.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.20,1:03:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessing carts have been set up \Nat a nearby border crossing, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.64,1:03:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with ten languages \Nregularly featured. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.34,1:03:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Many copies \Nare placed with visitors \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.91,1:03:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from countries \Nwhere our work is restricted. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.68,1:03:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes over 1,000 pieces of literature \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.11,1:03:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are placed in a single day \Nat the border crossing.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.25,1:03:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Nong Khai Congregation \Nhad the privilege \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.79,1:04:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of being a host congregation \Nwhen a special convention \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.26,1:04:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was arranged \Nin October of last year. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.86,1:04:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And during the convention, \Nthey were surprised and overjoyed to hear \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.63,1:04:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that the New World Translation \Nwas now available \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.74,1:04:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Thai language.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.34,1:04:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray that Jehovah continues to bless \Nthe brothers and sisters in Thailand.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.07,1:04:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of you around the world, \Nwe love you very much! \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.91,1:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \Nfrom Brooklyn, New York.\N
